                            <comment id="14478529" author="paulk" created="Sat, 30 May 2009 11:54:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Using &apos;&lt;tt&gt;this&lt;/tt&gt;&apos; inside a closure is potentially confusing - even though you would expect it to be transformed away in this case before being applied.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The workaround (which is also perhaps clearer) is to avoid this inside the closure altogether:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Category(Guy)
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Filtering {
    List process() {
        def myName = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.name
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.messages.findAll{it.name != myName}
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not saying that we don&apos;t need to have a well-defined semantics here - just pointing out alternatives.&lt;br/&gt;
You may already have found a similar workaround by now but searches may lead others here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467129" author="blackdrag" created="Sun, 31 May 2009 15:48:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &quot;this&quot; outside the closure should be the same as the &quot;this&quot; inside the closure. That was a decision we made long ago. I think that the transform simply does not handle ClosureExpression correctly. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467954" author="blackdrag" created="Wed, 30 Sep 2009 11:47:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
